_description: Humfrey Newton, a poem on the months — three stanzas rhyme royal

BodLatMisC66.First Lines:
Poites writen by derke parablesOf esperus breuely to
                    concludePhebus enforced in such likenesThat few men can espy by
                    similitude…
BodLatMisC66.Last Lines:
…and to leone has takyn his flightaugustus & phebus in
                    virgine is light

Robbins,  Rossell Hope.
